    To give an idea of the toys that  
are being played with by children in  
our village, we have made out the list
below.  We have included in the list  
some toys which would be used by very 
young children as well as toys which  
ll year olds would used.              
    Teddy Bears; Dolls; Bicycle (in   
the garage); Monopoly; Skipping Rope; 
Roller Skates; Bat and Ball; Football;
Paint Box; Comics; Felt Tip Pens;     
Snakes and Ladders; Ludo; Space       
Hoppers; lots of small Matchbox cars; 
Plasticine; Tin of Marbles; Lego;     
Pacman electronic game; Cluedo; Tree  
House; Connect 4; Exercise Books;     
Paper; Money Box; Pencil Case; Head   
Phones and Cassettes; Action Man; Toy 
Gun; Cricket Bat and a Computer with  
Space Invaders.
